    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Investigate and Modify\r\n\r\nExperiment with the program by making the following modifications, then run the program to observe the results.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO:</strong> What happens if you call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">recipesToString()</code> method? Add the following code segment to the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">RecipeRunner</code> class:\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background-color: #333333; color: white;\">\r\nSystem.out.println(\"Recommended vegetarian recipes:\\n\" + blog.recipesToString(r2, r3));\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nWhat is printed when you run the program? Why do you think this happened?\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> The recipes are stored in fixed fields instead of arrays. Explore how the method works without loops.\r\n</div>\r\n",
